Messages.Value: Thank you for contacting our travel agency. My name is Charlotte Martinez. How may I assist you today?
Hi Charlotte, my name is John Smith and I am calling because I have had a terrible experience with your agency during my trip from New York to Los Angeles.
I'm sorry to hear that, John. Can you please tell me what happened?

Well, first of all, my flight was delayed by several hours due to bad weather in New York. Then, when I finally arrived in Los Angeles, my luggage was nowhere to be found. I had to fill out a lost luggage form and I still haven't received any updates or information about my luggage.
I completely understand your frustration, John. Let me see if I can help you with tracking your lost luggage.
May I have your reservation number and date, as well as the airline you traveled with?
Yes, my reservation number is 1234567 and the date was February 10th. I traveled with American Airlines.
Thank you, John. I will contact American Airlines and get back to you as soon as I have an update. In the meantime, is there anything else I can assist you with?
No, that's all for now. Thank you for your help, Charlotte.
You're welcome, John. It was my pleasure to assist you today. Have a great day!
